Report: Analysis of Hotel Reservation Data¶

Introduction: This report, prepared by Mhammad Asif, presents an analysis of a hotel reservation dataset to gain insights into various aspects of the reservations.

# comparision of city and resort hotel cancelations and not cancell

plt.title('Reservation Status in Differents Hotels', size = 10)
plt.xlabel('hotel')
plt.ylabel('No of Reservation')

plt.show()

In [160]:
import calendar

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.title('Adr per month', fontsize=30)

# Get the month names
month_names = [calendar.month_name[i] for i in range(1, 13)]

# Use month_names as x-tick labels
ax = sns.barplot(x='month', y='adr', data=data[data['is_canceled'] == 1].groupby('month')[['adr']].sum().reset_index())
ax.set_xticklabels(month_names)

plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Value counts for overall data
overall_counts = data['market_segment'].value_counts(normalize=True)

# Value counts for canceled data
canceled_counts = canceled_data['market_segment'].value_counts(normalize=True)

# Plotting overall data
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.title("Market Segment Distribution - Overall Data")
overall_counts.plot(kind='bar')
plt.xlabel("Market Segment")
plt.ylabel("Proportion")
plt.show()

# Plotting canceled data
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.title("Market Segment Distribution - Canceled Data")
canceled_counts.plot(kind='bar',color='Green')
plt.xlabel("Market Segment")
plt.ylabel("Proportion")
plt.show()
